explains: v. 巧合，同时发生；一致，相符；相交，重叠
wordGroup: coincide with 符合；与...相一致
happen to coincide 不约而同；不谋而合

sentences.en: The interests of employers and employees do not always coincide.
sentences.cn: 雇主和雇员的利益并不总是一致的。

sentences.en: The kids' views on life don't always coincide, but they're not afraid of voicing their opinions.
sentences.cn: 孩子们的生活观未必总是一致，但是他们不怕表达自己的观点。
